        <Route path='/*' element={<Pnf/>}/>
      </Routes>
  - create componet folder and create header footer inside the component folder
  
  
  REDUX
  -----

  - actions are used to upadte state values in store
  - the output of action in reducer
  - to access values from store : action dispatch
    useSelector hook used to dispatch
       
  used to avoid props drilling (lifting method connects multiple componets to share data)
  redux create a storage space and provide data to components
  to install:
  redux-cart>npm install @reduxjs/toolkit
  npm i react-redux
  wrap the app function with provider (for provide redux store data to all components)
  <BrowserRouter>
      <Provider store={name-of-main-store}>
        <App />
       </Provider> 
    </BrowserRouter>
     
- create redux folder
- create a main store(nameStore)

    const productStore = configureStore({
    reducer:{
        productReducer : productSlice
    }
})

export default productStore
- the create a folder slice inside the redux
- create needed slices(product,cartetc.. like slices)

   const productSlice = createSlice({
    name :'products',
    initialState:{
        allProducts:[]
    }
   })

- now the value of product reducer is all product

AXIOS api call
--------------

api call is asynchronus(take delay to fetch data) so it cant do with reducer so

- create like this

   export const getAllProducts = createAsyncThunk('products/getAllProducts',async()=>{
    const result = await axios.get("https://dummyjson.com/carts")
   })
  
 - createAsyncThunk -action with asynchrouns function is called createAsyncThunk
 - product - it is in productslice name :'products',
  product means the value assigned to productSlice and in main store the value assigned to product reducer
 - getallproducts which page need the data they can call
 - axios for api call(get,put,post..) 

 - if a page need products call the getAllProduct function

 function Home() {
  const dispatch = useDispatch()// for useEffect to call function

  useEffect(()=>{
    dispatch(getAllProducts) // the function call to get all products 
  },[])
 }

- useDispatch() → allows us to send actions to Redux.

- useEffect() → runs only once when the page loads.

- dispatch(getAllProducts()) → calls the async function to fetch all products and store them in Redux.

extraReducer 
------------
createAsyncThunk to fetch data asynchronously, and then use extraReducers in a Redux slice to handle the thunk’s actions (pending / fulfilled / rejected) and update the Redux state.

  extraReducers:(builder)=>{
        builder.addCase(getAllProducts.fulfilled,(state,action)=>{   
            state.allProducts = action.payload - where the all product state is upadted
        }) }

action.payload = fetched data from api call (result.data.carts)

- but also upadte the loading and error states :-

upate initialState:{
        allProducts:[], fullfilled
        loading:true,   loading
        error:""        rejected 
    },

- to upadate state with respect to case :

builder.addCase(getAllProducts.fulfilled,(state,action)=>{   // action (function call) with fullfiled condition
            state.allProducts = action.payload
            state.loading =false
            state.error=""
        }) 
now we get the data in redux store

- to get data to componet (upadte data)
  
  import useselector

    const {loading,getAllProducts,error}=useSelector(state=>state.productReducer)
    in productReducer have object with 3 keys - loading,getAllProducts,error
